      "seed": 300028,
      "version": 235,
      "versionNonce": 381544911,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1781568579862,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For publishing to contrib (Will):\n  + Central, discoverable, marketplace-style catalog.\n  + Browse/restore/customize; default is one vetted option.\n\nAgainst / cautions (Nicole, Nithya):\n  − Cross-repo dependency complicates the release process\n  − Contrib has a lower review bar → trust/security risk;\n    type defs were already moved to core for this reason.\n − types.yaml and recipe-pack.bicep have overlaps. Reviewers have to make sure \n    types.yaml changes in radius repo has a corresponding recipe-pack.bicep change in \n    contrib repo and vice-versa\n  − Need clear line: vetted Radius-supported vs community/\n    experimental packs (user owns risk for non-vetted).\n\n\nAlternatives discussed:\n  • CLI emits the default pack as Bicep/YAML on demand.\n  • Keep a SAMPLE in contrib with 'may be stale' warnings.\n\nNext steps: Will documents scenario + aligns with Ryan;\nteam enhances CLI to output editable format.",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 2,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 14,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For publishing to contrib (Will):\n  + Central, discoverable, marketplace-style catalog.\n  + Browse/restore/customize; default is one vetted option.\n\nAgainst / cautions (Nicole, Nithya):\n  − Cross-repo dependency complicates the release process\n  − Contrib has a lower review bar → trust/security risk;\n    type defs were already moved to core for this reason.\n − types.yaml and recipe-pack.bicep have overlaps. Reviewers have to make sure \n    types.yaml changes in radius repo has a corresponding recipe-pack.bicep change in \n    contrib repo and vice-versa\n  − Need clear line: vetted Radius-supported vs community/\n    experimental packs (user owns risk for non-vetted).\n\n\nAlternatives discussed:\n  • CLI emits the default pack as Bicep/YAML on demand.\n  • Keep a SAMPLE in contrib with 'may be stale' warnings.\n\nNext steps: Will documents scenario + aligns with Ryan;\nteam enhances CLI to output editable format.",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "index": "aR",
      "autoResize": true
    }
  ],
